2003/4/17
- Finished TextFormator Framework Version 0.9 beta
- Finished "TextFormator Framework Introduction"

2003/5/5
- Updated "TextFormator Framework Introduction"

2003/5/10
- src/GeneralDefine.h: Removed enum TokenType, instead of std::string
- src/core/DefaultParseHandler.h, 
  src/extend/ConcreteParseHandlers.h, 
  src/extend/IndentFormatHandlers.h, 
  src/extend/CountFormatHandlers.h: Updated to use new token type
- src/core/LineFormator.*: Added method of register format handler for a set of types
- sample/*.cpp, 
  "TextFormator Framework Introduction": Updated to reflect changes above

2003/5/13
- src/extend/IndentFormatHandlers.h: Bug fix, modified WhitespaceFormatHandler::format to avoid a fatal error while there's a text line with only white spaces
- src/helper/FileFinder.*: Added a new helper class to traverse all files in specified directory and subdirectory
- src/Portability.h: Added a new head file used to platform portability configuration
- "TextFormator Framework Introduction": Updated to reflect changes above

2003/5/17
- Portability test: Under MSVC, g++, STLport platform
- src/helper/FileHelper.*: Modified the first "save" method(the first parameter "stream" should be a reference, not an instance), this mistake ignored by MSVC
- src/extend/ConcreteParseHandlers.h: Moved the declaration of counter variable out of "for" statement, this mistake ignored by MSVC, but regarded as a warning by g++

2003/5/18
- Updated "TextFormator Framework Introduction"

